  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n\r\nCommit hash : b437fab006b8df7d8622bbe5228050007e11d8c6\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\ncmd/rpcdaemon/commands/trace_filtering.go#L118\r\n\r\n```\r\n\ttraces, err := api.Transaction(ctx, txHash)       // same with api \"trace_transaction\"\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\treturn nil, err\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\t// 'trace_get' index starts at one (oddly)\r\n\tfirstIndex := int(indicies[0]) + 1\r\n\tfor i, trace := range traces {\r\n\t\tif i == firstIndex {\r\n\t\t\treturn &trace, nil\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn nil, err\r\n```\r\nWhy `firstIndex +1` here? When I was trying to get the first trace of a transaction i.e. `traces[0]`, should I use \"-1\" for the indicies parameter?\r\nAre we trying to remove the first trace? But in api \"trace_transaction\", all traces were included in the result.\r\n",
